<item>
            <title>[LU-13385] lnetctl: calculate Lustre traffic service-id </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13385</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In order to apply QoS on Lustre traffic , the service-id of the Lustre traffic needs to be added to qos-policy.conf and then mapped to the appropriate service level. There is no good way to identify what the service-id of the Lustre traffic is. This feature adds the ability to find the service-id from lnetctl by doing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
lnetctl service-id &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
